data.description: Newer construction in an unbeatable location, this is a prime property nestled in the heart of the action! Situated in a quiet historic neighborhood with a water view of McKay Bay. Overlooks DeSoto park which features an exercise trail, public pool, skate park, basketball courts, playground and soccer field. An oasis near the best sights and destinations the city of Tampa has to offer - only 2 miles from the port, channel side, and Sparkman wharf. Approximately 2 miles to Centro Ybor historic district and parking, where you can also pick up the trolley to all the sights. Only minutes to the best sights and attractions: University of Tampa; Museums; Curtis Hixon Park; Water Street; Riverwalk and Bayshore; Hyde Park; Tampa General Hospital; Armature Works. There is no HOA or CDD! This gorgeous gem was built in 2017 with only one owner. The home has been lovingly well-maintained. It has 4 bedrooms, 2 1/2 baths and 2 car garage with ample driveway space for guests. Stand-alone laundry room, and a large master suite which boast two walk-in closets, 2 sinks, and a separate toilet room. Builder upgrades include granite counters throughout, Venetian blinds on all windows, upgraded fixtures and a vinyl fence which encloses the backyard. In these days of soaring energy prices, the paid-off Tesla solar panels significantly reduce electric expenses. Raised covered patio in the back of the house to enjoy the outdoors and balmy Florida weather. Landscape highlights include a functioning butterfly garden and beautiful peach tree. Move-in ready home in a highly desirable area!
